# Root .dockerignore — applies when the build context is the repository
# root, which is the case for ALL builds in this repo today:
#   * apps/main-app/frontend/Dockerfile.prod
#   * agents/<name>/backend/Dockerfile{,.prod}        (need packages/agent-common)
#   * services/<name>/Dockerfile{,.prod}              (Phase 2+)
#
# Per-Dockerfile dockerignore files (BuildKit `Dockerfile.dockerignore`
# convention) live alongside each Dockerfile and trim the context further
# for that specific build. THIS file is the lowest common denominator —
# it must not exclude anything that any current build needs.

# --- VCS / editor ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vscode
.idea
.cursor/

# --- OS / temp ---
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# --- Node ---
**/node_modules
**/.vite
**/.cache
**/dist
.npm
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log

# --- Python build artefacts (safe to drop from every build context) ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/*.egg-info/

# --- App-specific build outputs (always safe to drop) ---
apps/main-app/frontend/node_modules
apps/main-app/frontend/dist
# Note: `agents/` and `apps/heliogram/` USED to be excluded here. They are
# now allowed because (a) every agent's Dockerfile builds from the repo
# root and needs `agents/<self>/backend/` in its context, and (b) the
# main-app build only COPYs `apps/main-app/frontend/` so the extra files
# only inflate the upload size by a few hundred KB, never the final image.
# Per-Dockerfile `.dockerignore` files trim the context further for builds
# that want it (e.g. main-app excludes other agents' code from its upload).

# --- Runtime / logs / local data ---
.runtime/
logs/
*.log
*.sqlite3
*.db

# --- Secrets (never leak into images) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.prod.example

# --- Docker itself ---
# Dockerfiles are passed to the daemon via `-f`; they don't need to ride
# inside the context. Exclude them plus any compose files from being
# baked into the image unnecessarily.
docker-compose*.yml
